description:
An All-New Marvel Now series. Continued from the groundbreaking Thor: God of Thunder series. After the events of Original Sin, Thor is no longer worthy of Mjolnir. But what happens when an all-new female Thor appears on the scene? Jason Aaron and Russell Dauterman take the series in a new direction staring a female Thor. The series lasted only 8 issues with 1 Annual and was replaced with the ThorS mini-series due to the events of Secret Wars, but returned as The Mighty Thor Volume 3 after the Secret Wars.

Collected Editions

  • Thor: The Goddess of Thunder (#1-5)
  • Thor by Jason Aaron & Russell Dauterman (#1-8)
  • A-Force Presents Volume 1 (#1)
  • A-Force Presents Volume 2 (#2)
  • A-Force Presents Volume 3 (#3)
  • A-Force Presents Volume 4 (#4)
  • A-Force Presents Volume 5 (#5)
  • A-Force Presents Volume 6 (#6)
  • Thor: Who Holds the Hammer? (#6-8)

deck: The original Guardians of the Galaxy are back!
description:
Guardians 3000 Volume 1

Dan Abnett returns to the Guardians of the Galaxy except this time, it's the original team featuring Vance Astro aka Major Victory, Charlie-27, Martinex, Starhawk, Yondu, and the newcomer Geena Drake, plus Rael Rider, the last remaining Nova in the 31st century. This series spins right out of the story from Guardians of the Galaxy Vol.3 issue 14.

The series ended with issue 8 due to the events of Secret Wars and was replaced with the "Korvac Saga" mini-series by the same writer. After Secret Wars, the original Guardians of the Galaxy return once more in the new ongoing Guardians of Infinity series.

Collected Editions

  • Guardians 3000: Time After Time (#1-5)
  • Korvac Saga: Wazones! (#6-8)

Translated into Spanish.
name: Guardians 3000

deck: An ongoing series about Bucky Barnes' new role in the Marvel Universe.
description:
Bucky Barnes: The Winter Soldier Volume 1

Writer Ales Kot and artist Marco Rudy are taking Bucky Barnes on his new mission after the events of ORIGINAL SIN. Bucky has become the new "man on the wall", taking out inter-dimensional threads with his partner (and former loyalist to Nick Fury) Daisy Johnson, better known as Quake. The series lasts for only 11 issues, but is continued (in a different form) a few months later in Thunderbolts Vol.3.

Collected Editions

  • Bucky Barnes: The Winter Soldier: The Man On The Wall (#1-5)
  • Bucky Barnes: The Winter Soldier (#6-11)
name: Bucky Barnes: The Winter Soldier
